Zerostation | Ga0 welcomes all of our friends to the screening of the film VIDEOPHILIA (and OTHER VIRAL SYNDROMES) by Peru filmmaker, Juan Daniel F. Molero.

We will discuss to Juan about his unique work after the screening. This will be, especially, a very good chance for the local filmmakers to approach the contemporary experimental filmmaking. 

About the work:
VIDEOFILIA (Y OTROS SÍNDROMES VIRALES), 103m
Director: Juan Daniel F. MoleroCountry
Production: Peru, 2015 

Juan Daniel F. Molero follows a group of youngsters in the suburbs of Lima and traces in the process a hallucinogenic journey in which the hybridization of the cinematic language and the audiovisual one gives rise to a formless and throbbing aesthetic that always stays loyal to the drive of the net. ANDREA MORÁN / FILMADRID

Trailer: https://vimeo.com/131297077

The film has won Tiger Award at 2015 International Film Festival Rotterdam. 

About the artist:
Juan Daniel F. Molero (b. Lima 1987) studied at Universidad del Cine in Buenos aires, is alumnus of IFFR Trainee Project for Young Film Critics 2010, Buenos Aires Talent Campus 2010, and Berlinale Talent Campus 2011. His first feature film Reminiscencias (2010), an autobiographical and neurological experiment, has screened in venues such as MoMA's Modern Mondays, BAFICI, Rotterdam, Art Museum of Lima, La Habana, Lima Independiente and FIDMarseille. His latest short film is Imagenotfound (2013) screened at Flaherty NYC, Valdivia Internatioanl Film Festival, and Lima Independiente Film Festival. He has curated and organized programs of avant-garde film for Cinema Tropical, Anthology Film Archives, Lima Independent Film Festival, MassArt Film Society, Art Museum of Lima (MALI), and Cine//B Festival in Chile. His second feature is "Videophilia (and other viral syndromes)", a micro budget fiction shot in his hometown between 2013 and 2014.


Free entrance.

